WarpControl is designed to coordinate Warp Vaults
This contract uses the OpenZeppelin contract Library to inherit functions from
Ownable.sol*
@dev Throws if called by any account other than a warp vault
@notice createNewVault allows the contract owner to create a new WarpVaultLP contract along with its associated Warp Wrapper Tokens*

WarpControl is designed to coordinate Warp Vaults
This contract uses the OpenZeppelin contract Library to inherit functions from
Ownable.sol*
@dev Throws if called by any account other than a warp vault
@notice createNewVault allows the contract owner to create a new WarpVaultLP contract along with its associated Warp Wrapper Tokens*

params._account: is the address whos collateral value we are looking up*

params._oracle: is the address for the UniswapOracleFactorycontract*

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params._amount: is the amount of LP being collateralized*
params._borrower: is the address of the borrower

checkTotalAvailableCollateralValue(addre.notice: checkCollateralValue is a view function that accepts an account address and returns the total USDC value of the accounts locked collateral

methods.constructor: the constructor function is fired during the contract deployment process. The constructor can only be fired once and is used to set up Oracle variables for the MoneyMarketFactory contract.

createNewLPVault(address,address,address.notice: createNewVault allows the contract owner to create a new WarpVaultLP contract along with its associated Warp Wrapper Tokens*

unlockColateral(address,address,uint256).notice: lockCollateralDown is an external function used to track locked collateral amounts globally as they decrease
